GOVERNANCE PROPOSAL
===================
ID:        vine-initial-2026-03-03
File:      core/vine.py
Tier:      T1 (core/)
Author:    Shiva + Sean Campbell
Date:      2026-03-03
Status:    PENDING


SUMMARY
-------
Implement VINE — the entity relationship layer.
Fills the stub in core/vine.py with a working three-layer entity model,
relationship tracking, and graph queries.

This is the direct answer to the gap exposed today:
"a personal AI that actually knows the USER."


THE THREE-LAYER MODEL
---------------------
L1 — Anonymous: type known, identity unknown. ("a person", "someone")
     Confidence low. No name stored. Used when we observe without knowing.

L2 — Reference: named or aliased, not fully verified.
     ("Sean", "my daughter", "the boss") Confidence medium.
     This is where most personal knowledge lives.

L3 — Named: fully identified, verifiable or consented.
     ("Sean Patrick Campbell", "Case 26-10177-j13")
     Confidence high. May link to external records (PRISM layer).

Promotion path: L1 → L2 → L3 as context accumulates.
Demotion: never automatic — only human can demote.
BLACK_BOX flag: L2/L3 entities can be flagged to suppress retrieval.


SCHEMA
------
Table: entities
  id             INTEGER PRIMARY KEY
  layer          INTEGER NOT NULL (1, 2, or 3)
  entity_type    TEXT NOT NULL  (person, project, concept, tool, place, event, legal)
  name           TEXT           (NULL for L1)
  confidence     REAL DEFAULT 0.5
  mention_count  INTEGER DEFAULT 1
  first_seen     TEXT NOT NULL
  last_seen      TEXT NOT NULL
  username       TEXT NOT NULL
  promoted_from  INTEGER REFERENCES entities(id)
  is_blackbox    INTEGER DEFAULT 0
  notes          TEXT

Table: entity_aliases
  id         INTEGER PRIMARY KEY
  entity_id  INTEGER REFERENCES entities(id)
  alias      TEXT NOT NULL
  source     TEXT
  UNIQUE(entity_id, alias)

Table: entity_relations
  id             INTEGER PRIMARY KEY
  entity_a       INTEGER REFERENCES entities(id)
  entity_b       INTEGER REFERENCES entities(id)
  relation_type  TEXT NOT NULL
  confidence     REAL DEFAULT 0.5
  evidence_count INTEGER DEFAULT 1
  first_seen     TEXT NOT NULL
  last_seen      TEXT NOT NULL
  username       TEXT NOT NULL
  UNIQUE(entity_a, entity_b, relation_type)


PUBLIC API
----------
init_tables(db_path)
  Create schema. Idempotent.

upsert(db_path, name, entity_type, username, layer=2, notes=None) → int
  Insert or update entity. Returns entity_id.
  On conflict (same name+username): increment mention_count, update last_seen.

link(db_path, name_a, name_b, relation_type, username, confidence=0.5) → int
  Create or strengthen a relationship between two entities.
  On conflict: increment evidence_count, update last_seen, raise confidence.

get(db_path, name, username) → dict | None
  Fetch entity by name (checks aliases too). Returns None if BLACK_BOX.

related(db_path, entity_id, relation_type=None, min_confidence=0.3) → list[dict]
  Get connected entities. Traverses both directions.

extract(text, username) → list[dict]
  Tier 1: regex against known entity patterns.
  Tier 2: fleet call (llm_router.ask) for open extraction.
  Returns list of {name, entity_type, layer} dicts.

promote(db_path, entity_id, new_layer, name=None) → bool
  Promote entity to higher layer. name required when promoting to L2+.

search(db_path, query, username, layer=None) → list[dict]
  Fuzzy name + alias search. Respects BLACK_BOX.

blackbox(db_path, entity_id) → bool
  Flag entity to suppress from retrieval. Irreversible without human action.


IMPLEMENTATION APPROACH
-----------------------
- Single SQLite file at artifacts/{username}/vine.db
- WAL mode, FK enforcement on
- Fleet generates implementation body (per CLAUDE.md mandate)
- Regex tier uses KNOWN_ENTITIES from old loam as seed
- No dependency on old Willow — clean build


WHAT THIS FIXES
---------------
Old Willow: entities table counts mentions. No relationships.
  Gemini + hardcoded query → [MISSING_DATA] on Sean's own bankruptcy.

VINE: entities have layers, relationships, confidence scores.
  RINGS routes by intent → VINE resolves "who" → LOAM retrieves "what".
  The system knows the user because it tracks how entities connect,
  not just that they were mentioned.


